<div><h3>ARTH 142 - Art and the Experience of Modernity, 1880-1940 </h3>  <hr>A survey of the major movements in avant-garde art from the late-19th century to World War II in Western Europe and the United States. We will examine how the art of this period&#8211;painting, sculpture, collage, photography, architecture&#8211;engaged the modern world through strategies as varied as resistance, subversion and open embrace. The course begins with the generation of neo- and post-impressionist painters, covers the development of abstraction and concludes with the surrealist dreamscape.<br><br><strong>Course Designation/Attribute:</strong> AP<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Offered every other year<br><br></div>		</td>
